casebody.data:
Catharine Donohue, Respondent, v. The Twenty-Third St. Railway Co., Appellant. Decided May 3, 1886. Appeal from judgment entered on verdict and from order denying motion for new trial. Robinson, Scribner & Bright, for appellant. Lindsay & Flammer, for respondent.

Before Sedgwick, Oh. J. and Freedman, J.

Per Ouriam.

Judgment and order affirmed, with costs.
